<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Gas Leak Prompts Airport Evacuation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) -- The main terminal of the Des Moines  
International Airport was evacuated today when a construction crew 
struck a natural gas line outside. 
</P>
<P>
	About 200 people were ordered out of the building after the  
10:30 a.m. accident, said fire department spokesman Ron Wakeham. No 
one was injured. 
</P>
<P>
	By 11:30 a.m., a crew from Mid-American Energy Co. had capped  
the 4-inch low-pressure gas line. Passengers were allowed back 
inside several minutes later. 
</P>
<P>
	Departing flights were delayed because of the evacuation.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
