<HEADLINE> Sean Elliott Awaits Word on Kidney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN ANTONIO (AP) -- Sean Elliott of the San Antonio Spurs will  
have to wait at least another two weeks before possibly undergoing 
a kidney transplant. 
</P>
<P>
	Elliott's brother has a kidney that appears compatible for a  
match, but commitments prevent him from traveling to San Antonio 
for another week or so, the San Antonio Express-News reported 
today. 
</P>
<P>
	When Elliott's brother arrives he will face several days of  
further tests to determine if he can be a donor. 
</P>
<P>
	Elliott has been working out to remain in good shape before  
surgery, the Express-News reported. The 31-year-old forward hasn't 
identified which of his two brothers is the potential donor. 
</P>
<P>
	Elliott wants to play for the Spurs after the transplant. He  
fought back from knee injuries and performed well this season in 
helping San Antonio to its first NBA championship. 
</P>
</TEXT>
