<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Monday on the New York Stock Exchange, Nasdaq Stock Market, 
and American Stock Exchange. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *Chicago Title Corp., up 5 5/16 at 48 1/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Fidelity National Financial Inc. will acquire Chicago Title, its  
larger rival, for $1.2 billion in cash and stock. The deal would 
allow the combined companies to cut between $65 million and $70 
million in costs in the first year. 

</P>
<P>
 *Perot Systems Corp., down 2 1/8 at 22 3/4    	
</P>
<P>
	A six-month lockup on insider stock sales expired Sunday,  
prompting selling. Following the company's initial public offering 
last February, company insiders and former officers had agreed not 
to sell shares until Aug. 1. 

</P>
