	The Skokie, Ill.-based company said second-quarter earnings will  
be significantly lower than Wall Street estimates of 7 cents a 
share as it works to transform its business from medical supplies 
and devices to a provider of Web-based medical systems. 

</P>
<P>
 *Collagen Aesthetics Inc., up 3 7/8 at 15 7/8    	
</P>
<P>
	Inamed Corp., a maker of breast implants and medical devices,  
will buy Collagen Aesthetics Inc. for about $142 million. The 
combined company will make a broad range of products for cosmetic 
treatments and reconstructive surgery. 

</P>
<P>
 *Varlen Corp., up 3 57/64 at 41 49/64    	
</P>
<P>
	Amsted Industries Inc. will acquire Varlen Corp. for about $790  
million, including about $50 million of assumed debt. Varlen makes 
products for heavy-duty automotive industries. Amsted is a 
diversified manufacturer of industrial products. 

</P>
