<HEADLINE> Predators Re-Sign Bob Boughner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- The Nashville Predators have re-signed  
restricted free agent Bob Boughner, making him the team's 
highest-paid defenseman. 
</P>
<P>
	Boughner, 28, signed a two-year, $1.8 million contract that will  
pay him $850,000 this season and $950,000 the following year, The 
Tennessean reported today. 
</P>
<P>
	Boughner had been scheduled to go to arbitration today in  
Toronto. 
</P>
<P>
	Boughner was selected by the Predators from the Buffalo Sabres  
in the 1998 expansion draft. The 6-foot, 205-pounder had 
career-highs with three goals and 10 assists in 79 games with 
Nashville last season. He also had 137 penalty minutes and recorded 
233 hits, fourth-best in the NHL. 
</P>
<P>
	The Predators still have two arbitration hearings scheduled.  
Defenseman Joel Bouchard is set for Wednesday and left wing Denny 
Lambert's is next Monday. 
  	   	
</P>
