<HEADLINE> China Captures 35,000 Suspects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BEIJING (AP) -- Chinese police have caught 35,000 suspected  
criminals in a month-long nationwide campaign to ensure stability 
ahead of the 50th anniversary of Communist Party rule, state media 
said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Police caught around 21,000 suspects just in the past five days,  
the official Xinhua News Agency said. 
</P>
<P>
	In all, more than 35,000 suspects have been caught since the  
campaign was launched July 1 to ``eliminate hidden troubles and 
create a better environment'' for the Oct. 1 anniversary and for 
China's resumption of sovereignty over the Portuguese enclave of 
Macau in December, Xinhua said. 
</P>
<P>
	Xinhua did not specify what sorts of crimes those arrested were  
suspected of committing. 
  	   	
</P>
