<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Fire Damages N.H. Abortion Clinic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GREENLAND, N.H. (AP) -- A fire damaged an abortion clinic that is  
often picketed by protesters. 
</P>
<P>
	The Feminist Health Center of Portsmouth sustained water and  
fire damage Sunday, when the clinic was closed. Police Chief Scot 
Blanchard said today the fire ``may be suspicious,'' but wouldn't 
elaborate. 
</P>
<P>
	The fire badly damaged a ramp providing access for the  
handicapped and charred a back corner of the building. 
</P>
<P>
	Diana Braun, the clinic's executive director, said anti-abortion  
protesters picket outside the building once or twice a week. 
</P>
<P>
	``We have, in the past month, gotten a couple of things in the  
mail that were anti-choice materials,'' she said. ``One of them was 
enough to be taken seriously.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The materials were turned over to police, she said.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
