<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Monday, Aug. 2, 1999    	

</P>
<P>
	Stocks Close Lower; Dow Down 9.19  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The threat of higher interest rates demolished a  
rally on Wall Street today, sending stocks lower even after a new 
report suggested the economy may not be overheating. The Dow Jones 
industrial average closed down 9.19 at 10,645.96. The index had 
risen as much as 136 points earlier in the session. Broader stock 
indicators also gave up early gains and finished lower. The Nasdaq 
composite index fell 14.86 to 2,623.63. Stocks, which incurred 
steep losses last week, had rebounded in early trading today after 
the National Association of Purchasing Management said the U.S. 
manufacturing sector grew in July for the sixth consecutive month, 
but not as strongly as most analysts expected. 

</P>
<P>
	Financial Figures  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures at the close:  
Dow Industrials:        10,645.96  -  9.19
NYSE Issues:         Advances 1,219  Declines 1,738  Unchgd  547
NYSE Volume:         611,200,720
