<CATEGORY> weather </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Showers and thunderstorms darkened the Plains on Monday, while  
sunny skies were seen in much of the East and West. 
</P>
<P>
	Low pressure brought showers across portions of western Texas,  
New Mexico, Kansas, southern Nebraska, and Iowa. The heaviest rain 
was located across portions of central and eastern Kansas. 
</P>
<P>
	A few scattered showers were seen across northern North Dakota  
and northwest Minnesota. A trough of low pressure extended west 
from the northern Plains and produced a few scattered showers 
across portions of Montana and Idaho. 
</P>
<P>
	Partly cloudy skies and dry conditions were seen from the  
Northeast, southward across the Mid-Atlantic region and into 
Southeast. 
</P>
<P>
	High pressure continued to hold across the western part of the  
nation as well. 
</P>
<P>
	A few scattered rain showers were seen across portions of  
Arizona, New Mexico, and northward across portions of western 
Nevada, Idaho and western Montana. 
</P>
<P>
	The West coast remained fair and dry from the Pacific Northwest  
southward through California and western Nevada. 
</P>
<P>
	Temperatures Across the Lower 48 ranged from a low of 41 in  
Jackson, Wyo., to an early-afternoon high of 99 in Huriburt, Fla. 
With the heat index, it felt like 127 in Huriburt. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
