<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> EU Approves Takeover of Hillsdown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) -- European Union regulators on Monday  
approved the $1.3 billion takeover by U.S. corporation Hicks, Muse, 
Tate and Furst Inc. of Hillsdown Holdings PLC, a British maker of 
furniture, canned food and other products. 
</P>
<P>
	``Given the companies' different lines of products and their  
limited market shares, the operation does not raise competition 
concerns,'' said a statement from the European Commission. 
</P>
<P>
	The EU executive agency said there was some potential overlap  
between the two companies in the European canned food market but 
not enough to provoke fears of an anti-competitive position. 
</P>
<P>
	Hicks, Muse confirmed in June it had beat British  
venture-capital group Candover Investments PLC in a bidding war for 
Hillsdown. The deal is the Dallas-based corporation's biggest in 
Europe. 
</P>
<P>
	The EU Commission checks all mergers and takeovers with a major  
impact on markets within the 15-nation bloc and can bar those 
deemed to inhibit fair business competition. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
