<DOCNO> APW19990802.0177 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-02 18:50:11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Angels Activate Edmonds From DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ANAHEIM, Calif.(AP) -- Anaheim centerfielder Jim Edmonds was  
activated from the 60-day disabled list Monday and was in the 
Angels lineup for the first time this season. 
</P>
<P>
	Edmonds, who missed all of the team's first 103 games, underwent  
arthroscopic surgery on April 19 to repair a torn labrum in his 
right shoulder. That injury, in addition to a strained right groin, 
forced him onto the DL for the fourth time in seven major league 
seasons. 
</P>
<P>
	The 29-year-old still hasn't been cleared by the Angels medical  
staff to play the field. He started against Kansas City as the 
designated hitter. 
</P>
<P>
	Edmonds made five rehab appearances with Single-A Lake Elsinore  
prior to being activated and went 8-for-19 with three RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
	To make room for him, Anaheim designated outfielder Reggie  
Williams for assignment. Williams, 33, batted .222 with a home run 
and 30 RBIs in 30 games this season. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
