<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Keller Set With Spanish Soccer Club </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MADRID, Spain (AP) -- United States goalkeeper Kasey Keller has  
finalized the details of a two-year contract with Spanish soccer 
club Rayo Vallecano and is expected to arrive at the team's Madrid 
base this week. 
</P>
<P>
	``I am very excited about playing in Spain after eight years in  
England,'' Keller said Monday in a U.S. Soccer Federation press 
release. 
</P>
<P>
	Keller played for the English first division club Leicester for  
the last three seasons. He is expected to be ready for Rayo 
Vallecano's opening match of the season on Aug. 22 against 
cross-town rival Atletico Madrid. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
