<HEADLINE> Robert Goulet To Star in Play </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Robert Goulet has been chasing windmills.  
</P>
<P>
	The Grammy-winning singer is playing the ultimate idealist, Don  
Quixote, in a California production of ``Man of La Mancha.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The play, produced by the Pacific Coast Theatre Group, began its  
statewide tour in Cerritos on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Goulet, who made his stage debut on Broadway as Sir Lancelot in  
the 1960 production of ``Camelot,'' has recorded more than 60 
best-selling albums. 
</P>
<P>
	Goulet, 65, just completed filming ``The Last Producer,'' with  
Burt Reynolds. He also finished voice-overs for an animated feature 
called ``Recess.'' Both films are scheduled to be released this 
year. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
