<HEADLINE> McGwire Ties Sosa With 41 Homers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Mark McGwire tied Sammy Sosa for the major  
league lead with his 41st home run -- and 498th of his career -- in 
the fifth inning of Monday night's game against the San Diego 
Padres. 
</P>
<P>
	With runners on first and third, McGwire hit his 14th homer in  
18 games on the first pitch from Woody Williams to give St. Louis a 
4-0 lead. The towering drive landed in the first few rows beyond 
the left-field wall and was measured at 368 feet. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire, who has seven RBIs in the last two games, struck out in  
the first and fouled out to the catcher in the third. He's 2-for-6 
for his career against Williams, with two home runs. 
</P>
<P>
	Earlier in the night, Sosa briefly took the home run lead by  
himself when he hit his 41st in a game against the Montreal Expos. 
  	   	
