<DOCNO> APW19990802.0233 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-02 17:30:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Sosa Critical of Hernandez Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Sammy Sosa met with Chicago general manager Ed  
Lynch on Monday after the outfielder was critical of the Cubs trade 
of Jose Hernandez. 
</P>
<P>
	The Cubs offered Hernandez a three-year contract late Saturday  
before the trading deadline but the infielder, who will be a free 
agent following this season, rejected it and was dealt to Atlanta. 
</P>
<P>
	``They should have taken care of him before,'' Sosa said after  
Sunday's game. ``They shouldn't have waited until the last minute. 
I'm really, really disappointed.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Hernandez and pitcher Terry Mulholland were traded to the Braves  
for pitcher Micah Bowie, who will start for Chicago on Tuesday, a 
minor league pitcher and a player to be named. 
</P>
<P>
	Lynch called Sosa into manager Jim Riggleman's office prior to  
batting practice Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	``When Sammy speaks, I listen,'' Lynch said later.  
</P>
<P>
	``(Lynch) explained everything to me,'' Sosa said. ``It's  
something I have to agree with.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Lynch told Sosa the Cubs had helped themselves for the future by  
acquiring the young players. 
</P>
<P>
	``I told him I want to be here for life and that I want to  
win,'' Sosa said. ``I don't want to play just for the money.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Sosa, who entered Monday night's game against Montreal tied with  
Mark McGwire for the major league lead with 40 home runs, made a 
promise to Cubs fans. 
</P>
<P>
	``I guarantee that next year we won't be in last place,'' Sosa  
said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
