<HEADLINE> Elliot's Transplant Weeks Away </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN ANTONIO (AP) -- It will be at least two weeks before San  
Antonio Spurs forward Sean Elliott can undergo a kidney transplant, 
according to a report. 
</P>
<P>
	Elliott's brother has a kidney that appears compatible for a  
match, but commitments prevent him from traveling to San Antonio 
for another week or so, the San Antonio Express-News said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Elliott's brother then will undergo several days of tests  
himself to determine if he can be a donor. It hasn't been revealed 
which of Elliott's two brothers is the potential donor. 
</P>
<P>
	The 31-year-old Elliott has been working out to remain in good  
shape before surgery, according to the Express-News. 
</P>
<P>
	The Arizona graduate has said he wants to play for the Spurs  
after the transplant. He fought back from knee injuries last season 
to help San Antonio win its first NBA championship. 
  	   	
