<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Thrashers Sign Free Agent Ferraro </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- The expansion Atlanta Thrashers, desperate for  
scoring punch heading into their inaugural season, signed 
free-agent center Ray Ferraro today. 
</P>
<P>
	Ferraro, 35, had 13 goals and 18 assists in 65 games for the Los  
Angeles Kings last season. Overall, the 15-year veteran has 346 
goals, 395 assists and 741 points during a career that also has 
included stints with Hartford, the New York Islanders and the New 
York Rangers. 
</P>
<P>
	``We are very happy to be adding a proven offensive player with  
Ray's ability to the organization,'' general manager Don Waddell 
said. ``He is an established NHL veteran who will lend a guiding 
influence to our younger players.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Ferraro has scored at least 20 goals during 10 seasons,  
including a career-high 40 with the Hartford in 1988-89. He played 
in the 1992 All-Star game as a member of the Islanders. 
</P>
<P>
	Terms of the deal were not immediately available.  
</P>
</TEXT>
