<HEADLINE> Actor Lamont Bentley Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Actor Lamont Bentley, who appears on UPN's  
``Moesha,'' was arrested at a party after a celebrity basketball 
game to raise money for the charity that bears his name. 
</P>
<P>
	Bentley, a Milwaukee native, was arrested Sunday morning on  
suspicion of disorderly conduct and obstructing and resisting an 
officer at the Empire Room, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	Bentley, 25, was released after his manager, Brian Perry, posted  
$450 bail. Perry did not respond to messages from The Associated 
Press on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	The actor plays Hakeem, a neighbor of Moesha, the title  
character played by pop star Brandy. The show's publicist, Marcy 
DeVeaux, declined comment. 
</P>
<P>
	Bentley was in Milwaukee for the Lamont Bentley ``Rebuilding  
Home'' Celebrity Basketball Game. The game was billed as benefiting 
the Lamont Bentley Foundations Inc., Bentley's organization that 
raises money for local charities. 
</P>
<P>
	A police report said Bentley became upset after a friend was  
taken into custody on suspicion of disorderly conduct. 
</P>
<P>
	``If you arrest him, you better arrest me,'' Bentley said,  
according to the police report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
